The evidence with the title 'Your total costs for health care: premium, deductible, and out-of ... ' says When choosing a plan, it's a good idea to think about your total health care costs, not just the bill ( the “ premium” ) you pay to your insurance company every month. Other amounts , sometimes called “ out-of-pocket ” costs, have a big impact on your total spending on health care – sometimes more than the premium itself . 
